Managing a business as an introverted creative who is very privacy-conscious should not be complicated, and yet, it sometimes is. Most online resources and coaches tell you to work with the big (and diabolical) technology companies using extraverted techniques. Advertise here, follow the algorithm, share who you are. Have your service checked out, be available 24/7, respond to questions with a video of yourself, respond immediately. Video, video, video.
01/03/2024
This is a transition year for me.
I don't want to feed my money, my data, and my energy to the big technology companies. Nor do I want coaches who have one extraverted solution that they apply to everyone. I'm exploring new ways to manage my business while fighting the idea I've long believed in, that things have to be done a certain way to succeed.
Wish me luck!
I have already taken the first steps.
I left FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
I also removed the last external tracker, Google Analytics, from my website yesterday and it feels good.
I recently subscribed to a Europe-based CRM for better GDPR compliance, and I will be migrating my business over the next few weeks.
I transferred my MX to Proton and I am now fully using SPF, DKIM, and DMAR, without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
03/03/2024
